rComments: Confusing lectures and disorganized powerpoints. Midterm and final were multiple choice. Gives comprehensive review guide for the finals then includes questions that were not covered in the review. Group project grading criteria unclear and frustrating. Don't buy the textbook.

M. Foth est très inspirant. Il connait bien sa matière et a beaucoup d'expérience en recherche au niveau des politiques et de la structure des systèmes de santé. C'est une personne facile d'approche et dynamique. Par contre, je ne peux pas nier que ses attentes sont vagues et mal déterminés ce qui peut engendrer de la frustration. Attention à APA**

Class was very confusing. Make sure to follow exam outline. Prof did his best to make class understand content but content is very dry.  Exams are based on classes, so make sure to go. I would suggest buying the textbook to clarify the theories he discusses in class.

Course (Theory in Nursing) is very frustrating.  Not a bad prof but not a highlight of the school.  Final project is reasonable.  Marks reasonably and TA's are helpful.  Textbook highly recommended to clarify course content.
Dr. Foth was a fantastic instructor! His teaching style is engaging and interesting. He was able to present some very challenging concepts in a way that was relevant and understandable. Great class!
Nice guy, did his best with the course material and a bit of a language barrier mixed with philosophical jargon. Pay attention to his exam review
